article.headline: IUPUI 87, Valparaiso 82 (OT)
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- George Hill scored seven of his 26 points in overtime to lead IUPUI to an 87-82 win over Valparaiso. IUPUI (13-7, 8-1 Mid-Continent) made 6-of-6 free throws in the final 23 seconds of the extra period. IUPUI trailed 45-25 at halftime, but outscored the Crusaders 47-27 in the second half. Hill scored four points in the first half, but poured in 15 in the second. He made a layup with 42 seconds left in regulation to tie the game at 72, but Brandon Cole missed a jumper with five seconds left that could have given the Jaguars the lead. Cole and Brandon Burks both scored 17 points for the Jaguars. Dan Oppland led Valparaiso (11-8, 4-5) with 27 points. Seth Colclasure scored 15 points and Mohamed Kone added 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Crusaders. IUPUI shot 30 percent from the field in the first half, but 68 percent in the second. The Jaguars outscored the Crusaders 25-9 from the free-throw line.
